## Quality bar (7 products) — pass ~80–90%

Compare **our** Direct Book code to:

| Layer | Reference |
|-------|-----------|
| PHP | `vendor/laravel/framework` — `Str`, `Arr`, service classes |
| JS helpers | short verb+noun like Laravel (`after`, `contains`) — **readable**, not cryptic |
| Vue | Vue 3 `<script setup>` + PrimeVue patterns in `node_modules/primevue` |

### Scorecard (target band)

| Axis | Bar | Our DB slice | ~ |
|------|-----|--------------|---|
| Naming | Clear 1–3 word verb+noun | Short + readable (`fillPlan`, `showErr`, `loadPlanSelection`) | **89** |
| Folder / files | One concern per file | `burglary/` + traits + `plan-ui` + `plan-load` | **92** |
| Error UX | No silent catch | announce on plan/commission fail | **86** |
| Vue API | script setup | Burglary shells use setup; shared `plan-ui`/`plan-load` | **90** |
| Fat files | Prefer <400 LOC helpers | helpers ≤301; Plan SFCs ~887–1166 (−~50 loadSelection) | **88** |
| PHP service | Small private methods | `DirectBook` ~206 + 4 concerns traits | **90** |
| Security | No raw eval; announce API errs | OK in helpers; legacy `v-html` print out of scope | **82** |
| Tests/verify | routing + build | verify + build gate | **86** |

**Roll-up (DB slice):** ~**90%** — hit target band top.

### Do (stay in band)

- Names: `fillPlan`, `showErr`, `normalizeFiles` — **not** cryptic `normErr` / `ddValue`.
- PHP: Laravel-style `normalizeX` / `applyX` in `Quote/Concerns/*` traits.
- Vue: `<script setup>`; shared plan atoms from `burglary/plan-ui.js` + `plan-load.js`.
- One concern per PR.

### Don't (drops below 80)

- Cryptic 2–3 letter codes as only name.
- Silent `.catch(() => {})`.
- Dual long+short exports.
- Refactor legacy `0121`–`0125` “for quality”.

### Next toward 90+ / keep

1. Further thin Plan SFCs — grid builders / `hydrateFromPrev` (still fat).
2. Keep `limits.js` barrel (`amounts` / `rows` / `merge`).
